For that matter umd.edu (University of Maryland at College Park) versus
umbc.edu (Baltimore County) -- the root problem is organizations attempt
to establish their claim to independance through these largely symbolic
but profoundly troublemaking power games.

We won't even talk about eng.umd.edu (our "Engineering" subdomain) or our
cs.umd.edu (Computer Science Department) subdomain.  My personal hope is
that once the patina fades and the magnitude of the continuing effort to
MAINTAIN these things becomes institutionally evident that domains will
re-devolve back to organizations geared to do first class management.

The truly tragic thing, brought home most forcefully by Mitch Snyder's
recent suicide, is that these fools squander so much effort and treasure
on trying to prove who has the biggest cojones when there are so many
IMPORTANT things that need to be done...

